Statement of Purpose

The laws of most jurisdictions throughout the world automatically confer
exclusive Copyright and Related Rights (defined below) upon the creator
and their initial successors and assigns (both initial and derivative)
as soon as a work is fixed in a tangible medium (e.g. a copy of a work
is recorded on a disk, a photographic film is developed, a painting
is completed, or a design is made digital or recorded in some other
medium). The Copyright and Related Rights in a Work are capable of
subsisting and are transferred, assigned and licensed as a singular,
inseparable unit and are not divisible by nature. The above licenses,
and the public domain dedication, are not intended to reduce, limit,
restrict, or condition any rights arising from copyright or other
intellectual property laws in the Work or any other features or
aspects of the Work. This public domain dedication is intended to
apply to the Work as a whole, and not to be subject to, nor to be
capable of being construed as, a license or limitation of any rights
under copyright law, or any other applicable law.

1. Copyright and Related Rights. A Work made available under CC0 may be
protected by copyright and related or neighboring rights ("Copyright and
Related Rights"). Copyright and Related Rights include, but are not
limited to, the following:

   i. the right to reproduce, adapt, distribute, perform, display,
      communicate, and translate a Work;
  ii. the right to Sui Generis Database Rights under the Directive
      96/9/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 11 March
      1996 on the legal protection of databases, as amended and/or
      succeeded, as well as essentially equivalent rights anywhere in
      the world;
 iii. the right to extract, reuse, reproduce, and exploit a database
      as a whole, or substantially in the entirety of the database;
  iv. the right to perform, adapt, or display a public performance or
      display, including by digital means; and
   v. other similar, equivalent or corresponding rights throughout the
      world based on applicable law or treaty, and any national
      implementations thereof.

